00:50:56.000 --> 00:50:58.000
Why? Really? Why?

00:50:58.000 --> 00:51:06.000
We know that Flemings were brought to Pembrokeshire in the 12th century

00:51:06.000 --> 00:51:15.000
As part of the English conquest of Wales, they would use colonists to settle land.

00:51:15.000 --> 00:51:20.000
There were a lot of Flemish mercenaries at that time too, weren't there?

00:51:20.000 --> 00:51:24.000
Yes. It's well documented in Pembrokeshire.

00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:26.000
That's interesting.

00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:35.000
I recognise that the morphology of Whitsun is very similar to villages in the low countries.

00:51:35.000 --> 00:51:36.000
Yes.

00:51:36.000 --> 00:51:42.000
That's as far as I got in the Gwent levels historic landscape study.

00:51:42.000 --> 00:51:43.000
How interesting.

00:51:43.000 --> 00:51:51.000
I gave a lecture at the University of Ghent probably about six years ago now.

00:51:51.000 --> 00:51:52.000
Yes.

00:51:53.000 --> 00:52:02.000
One of their brighter master students came up to me afterwards and said he was interested in...

00:52:02.000 --> 00:52:07.000
I had a slide about Whitsun and wondered if it was Flemish.

00:52:07.000 --> 00:52:08.000
Yes.

00:52:08.000 --> 00:52:13.000
This student, Gerven, went on to do it as his PhD.

00:52:13.000 --> 00:52:15.000
Wow, really?

00:52:15.000 --> 00:52:20.000
