00:52:50.000 --> 00:52:53.000
It's so nice when it's proved right though, isn't it?

00:52:53.000 --> 00:52:54.000
Yes.

00:52:54.000 --> 00:53:06.000
But I think those early speculations probably have been proved right through Gerven's PhD and also the research of this historian.

00:53:07.000 --> 00:53:20.000
I was thinking, Steve, I won't take much longer, looking at the Wendt Lug levels, which has been massively developed, how do you do your work there?

00:53:20.000 --> 00:53:23.000
Are you able to do anything there?

00:53:23.000 --> 00:53:35.000
The interest in the Wendt Lug level, and this goes back to John Allen again, he found a lot of Roman material.

00:53:35.000 --> 00:53:38.000
Off of what's called Rumney Great Wharf.

00:53:38.000 --> 00:53:40.000
It's a cardiff end.

00:53:40.000 --> 00:53:51.000
The Wendt Lug level has got this very strange landscape of lots of long, narrow fields, blocks sort of next to each other.

00:53:51.000 --> 00:53:56.000
It looks like it could be Roman in date.

00:53:57.000 --> 00:54:02.000
It's just gradually getting covered in development.

00:54:02.000 --> 00:54:04.000
It's a great loss.

00:54:04.000 --> 00:54:11.000
